III. PROJECT RENAMING OBLIGATION III. PROJECT RENAMING OBLIGATION (MANDATORY)

When you distribute a modified version of the Software as a STANDALONE PROJECT,
you MUST rename the project to a name that is CLEARLY DIFFERENT from the 
original project name.

For the purposes of this license, "PROJECT NAME" includes, but is not limited to:

1. Repository name (e.g., "DryfishLib")
2. Package/Namespace name (e.g., "com.dryfish.core")
3. Binary/Executable name (e.g., "dryfish-cli")
4. Display name (e.g., "DryFish Library")
5. Logo and branding elements
6. Any marketing terms used to identify the software
7. Domain names and URLs associated with the project
8. Social media handles (Twitter, GitHub, etc.)

"Clearly different" means:
- Different root words (e.g., "Fish" → "Shark")
- Different conceptual branding (e.g., "Dry" → "Wet")
- Visually distinct (not just changing case, spacing, or punctuation)

Examples of VIOLATION:
- "DryfishLib" → "DryFishLib" (only case change)
- "DryfishLib" → "Dryfish-Lib" (only hyphen added)
- "DryfishLib" → "DryfishLib2" (only number added)
- "DryfishLib" → "DRYFISH" (only case change)

Examples of COMPLIANCE:
- "DryfishLib" → "WetfishLib" (different word)
- "DryfishLib" → "SuperLogger" (completely different)
- "DryfishLib" → "BlueFish" (different branding)
